parameters.name: ClientToken
parameters.description:
The client token that is used to ensure the idempotence of the request.

You can use the client to generate the value, but you must ensure that it is unique among different requests.

>  If you do not set this parameter, the system automatically uses **RequestId** as **ClientToken**. **RequestId** of each API request may be different.

parameters.name: FinishWork
parameters.description:
Specifies whether the construction is completed. Valid values:

*   **true**
*   **false**

parameters.name: InstanceId
parameters.description: The ID of the Express Connect circuit.

parameters.name: LineCode
parameters.description: The circuit code provided by the connectivity provider.

parameters.name: LineLabel
parameters.description: The label of the cable in the data center.

parameters.name: LineSPContactInfo
parameters.description: The contact information about line O\&M.

parameters.name: LineServiceProvider
parameters.description:
The ISP. Valid values:

*   **China Telecom**
*   **China Unicom**
*   **China Mobile**
*   **Other ISPs in China**

parameters.name: RegionId
parameters.description:
The region ID of the Express Connect circuit.

You can call the [DescribeRegions](~~36063~~) operation to query the most recent region list.
